🔧 Software Part Overview

The software is responsible for:

Collecting data from sensors

Processing and analyzing conditions

Displaying real-time values

Alerting users when conditions go bad



---

🧩 1. Technologies Used

You can mention:

Frontend: React

Backend: Node.js 

Database: MongoDB 

Hardware Interface: ESP32



---

🔄 2. Data Flow

Explain like this:

1. Sensors collect:

Temperature 🌡️

Humidity 💧

Gas (if used, like ammonia)



2. Microcontroller (ESP8266/Arduino):

Reads sensor data

Sends data to server (via WiFi)



3. Backend Server:

Receives data through API

Stores in database



4. Frontend Dashboard:

Displays real-time values

Shows graphs & history





---

💻 3. Key Software Modules

📡 Data Acquisition Module

Reads sensor values

Converts analog → digital


🌐 Communication Module

Sends data using HTTP/MQTT

Example: REST API (POST /sensor-data)


🧠 Processing Module

Checks threshold values:

Temp > 30°C → Risk

Humidity > 70% → Spoilage risk



🔔 Alert System

Sends alert if conditions are bad:

SMS / Email / App notification



📊 Visualization Module

Dashboard showing:

Live readings

Graphs (daily trends)




---

🗄️ 4. Database Design (Example)

SensorData:
- id
- temperature
- humidity
- gas_level
- timestamp


---

⚙️ 5. Sample Logic (Pseudo Code)

if temperature > threshold_temp OR humidity > threshold_humidity:
    send_alert()
else:
    store_data()


---

📱 6. User Interface

Dashboard with:

Live readings

Status (Safe / Warning / Critical)

Graphs




---

🎯 7. Features

Real-time monitoring

Data logging

Threshold alerts

Remote access
